<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/6199861-jerry">Jerry</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I don&apos;t think 4-8th grade boys would be into this. It is too emotionally adult for them. Possibly 8th grade girls if they are the bookish sensitive ty<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I don't think 4-8th grade boys would be into this. It is too emotionally adult for them. Possibly 8th grade girls if they are the bookish sensitive type. There is cruelty and violence that is inappropriate for most children of current days. (Children of earlier generations could handle this because they were not raised like the snowflakes of today.)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
