<div id="review_4060395422" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4060395422" />
    <a title="harper!" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/96067457-harper"><img alt="harper!" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1615868708p2/96067457.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4060395422?book_show_action=true">Jun 22, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="harper!" class="user" itemprop="url" name="harper!" href="/user/show/96067457-harper">harper!</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/96067457-harper?shelf=2021">2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer4060395422&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4060395422" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12153743592568215054"><i>&quot;Grandmother, who had spent a thousand years in a jar, had finally chosen love. She had seen it, pure and simple and clean, seen it in the small beings of two gray cats and an old dog. Love in all its complexity and honor made a circle around them all.&quot;</i><br/><br/>if i had read this book when i was young i&apos;m sure i would be spilling over with whimsy now. what an intricate and beautiful story! ranger and puck and sabine live here, in my heart now. also, i love any exploration of the uniquely american mythos </span>
  <span id="freeText12153743592568215054" style="display:none"><i>"Grandmother, who had spent a thousand years in a jar, had finally chosen love. She had seen it, pure and simple and clean, seen it in the small beings of two gray cats and an old dog. Love in all its complexity and honor made a circle around them all."</i><br /><br />if i had read this book when i was young i'm sure i would be spilling over with whimsy now. what an intricate and beautiful story! ranger and puck and sabine live here, in my heart now. also, i love any exploration of the uniquely american mythos and this book delves into deep south bayou lore so elegantly. it felt like a bedtime story that would have terrified me and made me cry and made me love my mom so so much. truly "happyish and sadish" <br /></span>
